.TH MUSICLIB-CLI 1 "February 2026" "musiclib-cli 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
musiclib-cli \- Music library command-line interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B musiclib-cli
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B musiclib-cli
is a command-line dispatcher for the MusicLib music management system. It routes
commands to backend shell scripts for database operations, rating management,
mobile synchronization, and tag cleanup.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B rate \fIFILE\fR \fIRATING\fR
Rate a music file (1-5 stars). Updates the music library database.
.TP
.B mobile \fI[OPERATION]\fR
Manage mobile device synchronization (requires KDE Connect).
.TP
.B build
Rebuild the music library database from scratch.
.TP
.B tagclean \fIFILE\fR
Clean and normalize music file tags.
.TP
.B audacious \fI[OPERATION]\fR
Integrate with Audacious media player.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Rate a music file 5 stars:
.RS
musiclib-cli rate "/path/to/song.mp3" 5
.RE
.PP
Build the database:
.RS
musiclib-cli build
.RE
.PP
Clean tags in a file:
.RS
musiclib-cli tagclean "/path/to/song.mp3"
.RE
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success - operation completed
.TP
.B 1
User error - invalid input or precondition not met
.TP
.B 2
System error - unrecoverable failure (missing tool, I/O error)
.TP
.B 3
Deferred success - operation queued due to database contention
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/musiclib/musiclib.conf
User configuration file
.TP
.B ~/.local/share/musiclib/data/musiclib.dsv
Music library database
.TP
.B ~/.local/share/musiclib/logs/musiclib.log
Operation logs
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MUSICLIB_ROOT
Override the default musiclib root directory
.TP
.B MUSICLIB_CONFIG
Override the default configuration file path
